# Barrel File Export Patterns

**IMPORTANT**: Always use concrete named exports in barrel files (`index.ts`). Never use wildcard exports.

## ❌ Bad (Wildcard Exports)

```typescript
// index.ts
export * from './component';
export * from './service';
export * from './model';
```

## ✅ Good (Concrete Named Exports)

```typescript
// index.ts
export { MyComponent } from './component';
export { MyService } from './service';
export { MyModel, MyInterface } from './model';
```

## Benefits

- **Explicit API**: Clear visibility of what is exported from each module
- **Better Tree-shaking**: Bundlers can optimize unused exports more effectively
- **Improved IDE Support**: Better autocomplete and refactoring
- **Prevents Name Collisions**: Reduces risk of accidentally exporting internal symbols
- **Easier Maintenance**: Explicitly see what's part of the public API

## Implementation

When creating barrel files, list each export explicitly:

```typescript
// admin/index.ts
export { AdminModule } from './admin.module';
export { LandingComponent } from './landing.component';
export { AccessComponent } from './access/access.component';
```
